1 (2) THE PRESUMPTION DESCRIBED IN PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS
2 SUBSECTION MAY BE REBUTTED BY CLEAR AND CONVINCING EVIDENCE THAT THE
3 STATEMENT WAS VOLUNTARY AND NOT MADE IN RESPONSE TO THE FALSE
4 INFORMATION USED BY THE LAW ENFORCEMENT OFFICER TO ELICIT THE
5 STATEMENT.
6 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
7 October 1, 2025.

